JSON_SETTINGS.query:
###########################################################
# List of User Sessions
###########################################################
| paramdefaults
	application = "%"
	user = "%"
	timestep = 60  # amount of time for shifting the timeframe
	timeunit = 'm' # unit of time for shifting the timeframe
	pagesize = 5000
	pagemax = 1000
| globals
	INITIAL_LATEST = latest()
	CREDENTIALS = $environment$
	QUERY = encode(`
SELECT 
	  userSessionId
	, userId
	, startTime
	, endTime
	, duration
	, userevent.page
	, useraction.application 
FROM usersession
WHERE useraction.application LIKE "`+param(application, "%")+`"
  AND userId  LIKE "`+param(user, "%")+`"
`)

| source web 
	url= globals(CREDENTIALS).url + "/api/v1/userSessionQueryLanguage/table?"
			+"query="+globals(QUERY)
			+"&addDeepLinkFields=false"
			+"&explain=false"
			+"&startTimestamp="+earliest()
			+"&endTimestamp="+latest()
			+"&pageSize=" + param(pagesize)
	
	headers = object( "Authorization" "Api-Token "+ globals(CREDENTIALS).password )
	
	pagination 	= true # enable pagination
	
	pageinitial = latestSet(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # initial page value 
	
	page 		= timeframeOffset(0, param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # adjust the initial value every time
				  
	pageend 	= ( 
					 latest() > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
					 OR timeOffset(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
				  ) # return true when end condition has been reached
	
	pagemax 	= param(pagemax) # the max number of pages to fetch, prevents endless loops
	
| filter length(values) > 0 AND isUndef(error)	
| unbox values
| set
	# https://dynatrace.yourcompany.com/e/1234abcd-5d58-xxxx-yyyy-123456789/ui/user-sessions/query?gtf=-100d%20to%20now&gf=all&sessionquery=
	# Query Example: SELECT * FROM usersession WHERE userSessionId ="xxx"
	"Dynatrace" = globals(CREDENTIALS).url 
			+ "/ui/user-sessions/query?gtf=-100d%20to%20now&gf=all&sessionquery="
			+ encode('SELECT * FROM usersession WHERE userSessionId ="' +values[0] + '"')
			
	"EMP" = "/app/dashboard/view?id=28&session_id=" + values[0]
			+"&environment=" + encode(`$environment$`)
			+"&earliest=" + earliest()
			+"&latest=" + latest()
	
	"userID" = values[1]
	"starttime" = values[2]
	"endtime" = values[3]
	"duration" = values[4]
	"pages" = values[5]
	"applications" = values[6]
| remove columnNames, values, extrapolationLevel
| formatfield 
	[columnNames, pages, applications] = list
	[starttime, endtime] = timestamp
	duration = ['duration', "ms"]
	"Dynatrace"= ['link', "Dynatrace", "button", "fa-external-link-square-alt", "blank"]
	"EMP"= ['link', "EMP", "button", "fa-external-link-square-alt", "blank"]
| sort count reverse=true
| display 
	download = true

###########################################################
# Session Experience Score By Application
###########################################################
| paramdefaults
	application = "%"
	user = "%"
	timestep = 60  # amount of time for shifting the timeframe
	timeunit = 'm' # unit of time for shifting the timeframe
	pagesize = 5000
	pagemax = 1000
| globals
	INITIAL_LATEST = latest()
	CREDENTIALS = $environment$
	QUERY = encode(`
SELECT 
	  useraction.application as application
	, COUNT(*) as "Count"
	, userExperienceScore
FROM usersession 
WHERE useraction.application LIKE "`+param(application, "%")+`"
  AND userId  LIKE "`+param(user, "%")+`"
GROUP BY userExperienceScore, application
`)

| source web 
	url= globals(CREDENTIALS).url 
			+ "/api/v1/userSessionQueryLanguage/table?"
			+"query="+globals(QUERY)
			+"&addDeepLinkFields=false"
			+"&explain=false"
			+"&startTimestamp="+earliest()
			+"&endTimestamp="+latest()
			+"&pageSize=" + param(pagesize)
	
	headers = object( "Authorization" "Api-Token "+ globals(CREDENTIALS).password )
	
	pagination 	= true # enable pagination
	
	pageinitial = latestSet(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # initial page value 
	
	page 		= timeframeOffset(0, param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # adjust the initial value every time
				  
	pageend 	= ( 
					 latest() > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
					 OR timeOffset(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
				  ) # return true when end condition has been reached
	
	pagemax 	= param(pagemax) # the max number of pages to fetch, prevents endless loops
	
| filter length(values) > 0 AND isUndef(error)
| unbox values
| set
	"Application" = values[0]
	"count" = values[1]
	"score" = values[2]
| stats
	by = [Application]
	TOTAL = sum(count)
	SATISFIED = sumif(count, ("score" == "SATISFIED"))
	TOLERATED = sumif(count, ("score" == "TOLERATED"))
	FRUSTRATED = sumif(count, ("score" == "FRUSTRATED"))
| sort Application
| set 
	"SATISFIED %"  = ( 1.000 * SATISFIED / TOTAL) * 100
	"TOLERATED %"  = ( 1.000 * TOLERATED / TOTAL) * 100
	"FRUSTRATED %" = ( 1.000 * FRUSTRATED / TOTAL) * 100
	"Apdex Score"  = round( (SATISFIED + (TOLERATED * 0.5) ) / TOTAL, 2)

| formatfield
	"Apdex Score" = ['threshold', 0.94, 0.85, 0.7, 0.49, 0, "bg"]
	"Apdex Score" = ['decimals', 2]
	
	[ "TOTAL"
	, "SATISFIED"
	, "TOLERATED"
	, "FRUSTRATED"] = ['separators', "'", "3"]
	
	["SATISFIED %"
	, "TOLERATED %"
	, "FRUSTRATED %"] = [ 
							  ['decimals', 1]
							, ['postfix', " %"]
						]
						
	fields() =  ['align', "right"]				

| display download = true

widgets.TITLE: Top Action Durations for Actions >= Minimum Duration

JSON_SETTINGS.query:
###########################################################
# Top Action Durations for Actions >= Minimum Duration
###########################################################
| paramdefaults
	application = "%"
	user = "%"
	timestep = 60  # amount of time for shifting the timeframe
	timeunit = 'm' # unit of time for shifting the timeframe
	pagesize = 5000
	pagemax = 1000
	minimum_duration = 3000
| globals
	INITIAL_LATEST = latest()
	CREDENTIALS = $environment$
	QUERY = encode(`
SELECT 
	domain
	, name
	, TOP(targetURL, 10) as "TopURLs"
	, type
	, count(*) as "ActionCount"
	, avg(duration)
	, avg(networkTime)
	, avg(serverTime)
	, avg(visuallyCompleteTime)
FROM useraction 
WHERE duration >= `+param(minimum_duration, 3000)+`
  AND useraction.application LIKE "`+param(application, "%")+`"
  AND usersession.userId  LIKE "`+param(user, "%")+`"
GROUP BY 
	  domain
	, name
	, type 
`)

| source web 
	url= globals(CREDENTIALS).url 
			+ "/api/v1/userSessionQueryLanguage/table?"
			+"query="+globals(QUERY)
			+"&addDeepLinkFields=false"
			+"&explain=false"
			+"&startTimestamp="+earliest()
			+"&endTimestamp="+latest()
			+"&pageSize=" + param(pagesize)
	
	headers = object( "Authorization" "Api-Token "+ globals(CREDENTIALS).password )
	pagination 	= true # enable pagination
	
	pageinitial = latestSet(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # initial page value 
	
	page 		= timeframeOffset(0, param(timestep), param(timeunit)) # adjust the initial value every time
				  
	pageend 	= ( 
					 latest() > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
					 OR timeOffset(earliest(), param(timestep), param(timeunit)) > globals(INITIAL_LATEST)
				  ) # return true when end condition has been reached
	
	pagemax 	= param(pagemax) # the max number of pages to fetch, prevents endless loops
	
| filter length(values) > 0 AND isUndef(error)
| unbox values
| set
	"domain" 					= values[0]
	"type" 						= values[3]
	"name" 						= values[1]
	"Action Count"				= values[4]
	"avg(duration)" 			= values[5]
	"total(duration)"			= "Action Count" * "avg(duration)"
	"avg(networkTime)" 			= values[6]
	"avg(serverTime)" 			= values[7]
	"avg(visuallyCompleteTime)" = values[8]
	"Top URLs" 					= values[2]
	
| remove extrapolationLevel, columnNames, values
| sort "total(duration)" reverse = true

| formatfield
	"Top URLs" = list
	"name" = [ ['css', "max-width", "30vw"] 
			 , ['css', "overflow-x", "auto"]
			 ]
	[ "avg(duration)" 
	, "avg(networkTime)"
	, "avg(serverTime)" 
	, "avg(visuallyCompleteTime)"
	]
		= [  ['decimals', 0], ['separators'], ['align', right], ['postfix', ' ms'] ]
	
	"Action Count" = [  ['separators'], ['align', right] ]
	 
	"total(duration)" = ['duration', "ms"]
									
| display download = true

JSON_AFFECTED_WIDGETS.376: Top Action Durations for Actions >= Minimum Duration

JSON_SETTINGS.content: IMPORTANT: This dashboard will make a lot of calls to the Dynatrace API. Each widget will make one call for every '$timestep$$timeunit$' in the timeframe you have selected. It is recommended to not choose timeframes higher than 24 hours.

parameters.LABEL: Query Select
parameters.NAME: application
parameters.VALUE:
###########################################################
# Get List of Applications active in the last 1 month
###########################################################
| globals
	CREDENTIALS = $environment$
	QUERY = encode(`SELECT DISTINCT application
					FROM useraction
					ORDER BY application`)
;
| meta name = "applications"
| source web 
	url= (
		globals(CREDENTIALS).url + "/api/v1/userSessionQueryLanguage/table?"
										+"query="+globals(QUERY)
										+"&addDeepLinkFields=false"
										+"&explain=false"
										+"&startTimestamp="+now(null, -1, "M")
										+"&endTimestamp="+now()
										+"&pageSize=5000"
	)
	headers = object( "Authorization" "Api-Token "+ globals(CREDENTIALS).password )
| unbox values
| set 
	"VALUE" = values[0]
	"LABEL" = values[0]
| keep VALUE, LABEL
;
| mimic name="applications"
| set 
	LABEL = substring(LABEL, 0, indexOf(LABEL, " [" ))
	VALUE = LABEL+"%"
| distinct VALUE
;
| resultconcat
| sort LABEL
;
| resultconcat
| record
	["VALUE", "LABEL"]
	["%", "All Applications"]
